Lecture 3

Set up

The required packages can be loaded with the chunk below.

using <- function(...) {
    libs <- unlist(list(...))
    need <- libs[!unlist(lapply(libs, require, character.only = T))]
    if(length(need) > 0){ 
        install.packages(need, repos = "https://cloud.r-project.org")
        need <- need[!unlist(lapply(need, require, character.only = T))]
        if (length(need) > 0) {
          if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = T))
            install.packages("BiocManager")
          BiocManager::install(need)
        }
    }
}
using("ggplot2", "dplyr", "ggseqlogo", "GenomicRanges",
      "BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19", "biomaRt")

Gene annotations

As an R implementation of the BioMart project, biomaRt facilitates access to a variety of resources ranging from Ensembl Genomes to the COSMIC cancer database. The chunk below retrieves the Ensembl gene set, subsets autosomal genes with valid HGNC symbols, converts the chromosome names to UCSC scheme, and finally derives a GRanges object from it.

Construction

mart <- useMart(biomart = "ENSEMBL_MART_ENSEMBL", host = "grch37.ensembl.org",
                 path = "/biomart/martservice", dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl")
si <- Seqinfo(genome = "hg19")[paste0("chr", 1:22)]
genes <- getBM(attributes = c("hgnc_symbol", "chromosome_name", "start_position",
                              "end_position", "strand", "ensembl_gene_id"),
        filters = "chromosome_name", values = as.character(1:22), mart = mart) %>%
  arrange(chromosome_name, start_position) %>%
  filter(hgnc_symbol != "") %>%
  mutate(strand = ifelse(strand == 1, '+', '-'),
         chromosome_name = paste0('chr', chromosome_name)) %>%
  makeGRangesFromDataFrame(keep.extra.columns = T,
                           start.field = "start_position",
                           end.field = "end_position",
                           seqinfo = si)

Sequence analysis

GC content around TSS

set.seed(42)
genes.sub <- genes[strand(genes) == '+'] %>%
  sample(1000)
promoters(genes.sub, upstream = 1e3, downstream = 1e3) %>%
  getSeq(BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19, .) %>%
  consensusMatrix(as.prob = T) %>%
  .[c('C','G'),] %>%
  colMeans() %>%
  data.frame(y = .) %>%
  mutate(x = 1:n() - 1e3) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x, y)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0) +
  geom_point(color = 'blue', alpha = .2) +
  geom_smooth(color = 'red') +
  labs(x = 'distance to TSS',
       y = 'GC content')

Characteristic of splice acceptors

exons.sub <- getBM(attributes = c("ensembl_exon_id", "exon_chrom_start", "exon_chrom_end",
                              "chromosome_name", "strand"), filters = "ensembl_gene_id",
               values = genes.sub$ensembl_gene_id, mart = mart) %>%
  arrange(chromosome_name, exon_chrom_start) %>%
  mutate(strand = ifelse(strand == 1, '+', '-'),
         chromosome_name = paste0('chr', chromosome_name)) %>%
  makeGRangesFromDataFrame(keep.extra.columns = T,
                           start.field = "exon_chrom_start",
                           end.field = "exon_chrom_end",
                           seqinfo = si)

resize(exons.sub, fix = 'start', width = 10) %>%
  resize(fix = 'end', width = 20) %>%
  getSeq(BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19, .) %>%
  consensusMatrix() %>%
  .[c('A', 'C', 'G', 'T'),] %>%
  ggseqlogo()
